Vwhat are these things to the right of my terminal?  

Those are terminal tabs/sessions in your IDE. Each entry is a separate terminal session. You likely have:
Multiple zsh sessions (shell instances)
Cursor (npm run) — a terminal running npm run dev
Cursor (cd /Users/gypsyadmin/ge...) — terminals that changed directory
These can accumulate from:
Opening new terminals
Background commands
Previous sessions that weren’t closed
Since we killed the extra Vite processes, you can close unused terminal tabs. Right-click a tab and select "Kill Terminal" or click the trash icon.
To keep it clean:
Use one terminal for the dev server (npm run dev)
Close any others you don’t need
